      <h2>Conclusion</h2>
      <p>The framing nailer market has split into clear tiers. For production crews who need maximum nails per charge and cordless freedom, the Milwaukee 2743-20 and DEWALT DCN692B are the top contenders. The Milwaukee delivers more power per stroke for engineered lumber, while the DEWALT delivers more nails per battery charge for crews who frame all day without stopping. For crews who value light weight above all and are willing to manage fuel cell costs, the Paslode 905600 remains the standard for roofers and production framers who cover large square footage quickly. And for teams that already run compressors, the Metabo HPT NR90ADES1 at 4.9 pounds is the obvious choice: it is light enough to carry all day, reliable enough to run for years without major maintenance, and affordable enough to equip a full crew. Match the power type to your crew's workflow, and always keep a spare magazine and a can of lubricant in the gang box.</p>

